comment.author: 47524421@N08
comment._content: Five Boeing 203 trainers of the Boeing School of Aeronautics, the closest being Boeing 203A (203B) NC13392 c/n 1986, built by the Boeing School as a Model 203A with a Wright J-6-5 engine instead of the Axleson engine of the 203, but converted to 203B standard with a further engine change to a Lycoming R-680.
